1. ✅ Project Case Studies (Not Just Portfolio Cards)
Why: MNCs look for real-world impact, process, and problem-solving.

🔹 Add 2–3 featured projects with:

Project Goal

Your Role

Tools Used

Challenges & Solutions

Screenshots or short demo

GitHub/live link

🔸 Bonus: Add tags like “React”, “API Integration”, “Responsive”, etc.

2. ✅ Testimonials or Endorsements
Builds trust and shows professional experience.

Add quotes from:

Clients

Former team leads/managers

Mentors

Include photo (optional) and name/company.

3. ✅ Professional Resume + Download Button
Quick access for HRs and recruiters.

Add a “View Resume” and “Download PDF” button in hero or about section.

Highlight key resume points (experience, strengths, achievements).

4. ✅ Experience Timeline / Career Path
MNCs value growth and commitment.

Use a vertical timeline to show:

Freelance work

Training/certifications

Projects you’ve worked on

Milestones

5. ✅ Technologies/Tools Grid
Helps HRs quickly scan your stack.

Use logos or icons for:

HTML, CSS, JS, React, Git, Bootstrap, etc.

Separate into categories: Front-End, Tools, Design

6. ✅ "Why Hire Me" Section
Shows personality and confidence.

Short paragraph or bullet points:

Reliable and fast delivery

Focus on user experience & responsive design

Proven ability to work with teams and clients

Constant learner, great communicator

7. ✅ Certifications & Achievements
MNCs love verified skills.

List things like:

React certificate from Coursera/Udemy

Frontend Mentor challenges

GitHub streaks or contributions

8. ✅ Blog / Insights (Optional)
Thought leadership. Shows you care about learning & sharing.

Share articles on:

Front-end best practices

Design systems

Accessibility

Even 2–3 posts help.

9. ✅ Contact Section with Personality
Add a short line like:
"Let's build something great together."

Include:

Contact form

Email

LinkedIn

GitHub

10. ✅ Awards / Recognition (Optional but Impressive)
Add anything like:

“Top performer in XYZ internship”

“Contributor to open-source projects”

🧠 Bonus UX Tips:
Use soft animations (scroll-in, fade, hover)

Keep a clean, modern design

Responsive on all screen sizes

Dark/light mode (optional but trendy)

🔚 Final Call-to-Action Section:
Something like:
“Ready to collaborate or hire me? Let’s connect.”
Include buttons for LinkedIn, GitHub, and email.